  "name": "Tactical Reposition",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/feats/dodge.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You excel at moving foes right where you want them.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Int 13, Combat Expertise, Improved Reposition.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>When making a reposition combat maneuver (Pathfinder RPG Advanced Player's Guide 322), you can move an enemy into a trap or other hazardous area, such as a pit, wall scythe, or blade barrier. When you do so, the moved enemy is treated as though it had activated the trap or triggered the hazard, and it takes a -2 penalty to AC and on saving throws to mitigate the trap or hazard's effects.<br/><br/><b>Normal</b><br/>You cannot reposition a foe into an intrinsically dangerous space such as a pit or blade barrier.",
